Here are the public test cases for feature8_3_manifest_formatting:
{
  "description": "Formatting preservation when rewriting the primary manifest. When the recorded version inside the primary manifest is updated, the file's original whitespace style is preserved: the existing indentation unit (tab or a run of spaces) and the existing line-ending style (line feed, or carriage-return plus line feed) are kept unchanged, and a single trailing newline is ensured. Input supplies the exact raw text of the primary manifest before the release; output reports the exact raw text of the manifest after the version bump, as a JSON-quoted string.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "kind": "release",
        "manifestText": "{\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n}\n",
        "ops": [
          {
            "commit": "feat: c"
          }
        ],
        "args": [],
        "report": [
          "manifest_raw"
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "manifest_raw=\"{\\n  \\\"version\\\": \\\"1.1.0\\\"\\n}\\n\"\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "kind": "release",
        "manifestText": "{\n\t\"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n}\n",
        "ops": [
          {
            "commit": "feat: c"
          }
        ],
        "args": [],
        "report": [
          "manifest_raw"
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "manifest_raw=\"{\\n\\t\\\"version\\\": \\\"1.1.0\\\"\\n}\\n\"\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the public test cases for feature9_1_tag_fallback:
